{"id":"1910.06577","submitter":"Jiahao Huang","authors":"Min Zhuang, Jiahao Huang, Chaohong Lee","title":"Simultaneous measurement of DC and AC magnetic fields at the Heisenberg\n  limit","comments":"15 pages, 7 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. Applied 13, 044049 (2020)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevApplied.13.044049","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.atom-ph quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  High-precision magnetic field measurement is an ubiquitous issue in physics\nand a critical task in metrology. Generally, magnetic field has DC and AC\ncomponents and it is hard to extract both DC and AC components simultaneously.\nThe conventional Ramsey interferometry can easily measure DC magnetic fields,\nwhile it becomes invalid for AC magnetic fields since the accumulated phases\nmay average to zero. Here, we propose a scheme for simultaneous measurement of\nDC and AC magnetic fields by combining Ramsey interferometry and rapid periodic\npulses. In our scheme, the interrogation stage is divided into two signal\naccumulation processes linked by a unitary operation. In the first process,\nonly DC component contributes to the accumulated phase. In the second process,\nby applying multiple rapid periodic $\\pi$ pulses, only the AC component gives\nrise to the accumulated phase. By selecting suitable input state and the\nunitary operations in interrogation and readout stages, and the DC and AC\ncomponents can be extracted by population measurements. In particular, if the\ninput state is a GHZ state and two interaction-based operations are applied\nduring the interferometry, the measurement precisions of DC and AC magnetic\nfields can approach the Heisenberg limit simultaneously. Our scheme provides a\nfeasible way to achieve Heisenberg-limited simultaneous measurement of DC and\nAC fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2019 07:56:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 Feb 2020 04:57:51 GMT"}],"u