ses derived from radial velocities and transit timing variations is\nconnected to the radius distribution features we have identified. Altogether,\nthe calculations in this work confirm that tidal dissipation has non-negligible\nconsequences for the structural properties of short-period sub-Neptunes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2019 14:20:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Oct 2019 20:56:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-04"}
